headline: Teledyne (TDY): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q2 Earnings?
summary: Teledyne’s 11.7% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 6.3%, and its stock price has climbed to $557.57 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
